Catalyst-Plugin-Widget

Termin 'widget' means kind of object that knows about current Catalyst
context and can be easily stringified to text representation.

A typical example of a widget - CatalystX::Widget::Paginator module.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Catalyst::Plugin::Widget

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Catalyst-Plugin-Widget

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Catalyst-Plugin-Widget

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Catalyst-Plugin-Widget

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Catalyst-Plugin-Widget/


